.SH NAME
.B simple_shell \- A Simple Shell Holberton Project

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B ./hsh
.PP

.SH Description
A simplified CLI, akin to any other standard Linux shell. Can run in interactive and non-interactive mode. Non-interactive mode enables scripting and pipes.

.SH OVERVIEW
simple_shell takes, pipes, interprets and executes commands from files and the command line.

.SH USAGE
IT IS RECOMMENDED THE USER MAKES SURE THEY HAVE THE GNU COMPILER COLLECTION OR EQUIVALENT BEFORE ATTEMPTING TO RUN!
To compile and run simple_shell, please enter the following into your existing shell:
.P
.RS
.B gcc -Wall -Werror -Wextra -pedantic *.c -o hsh
.P
.RE
After compilation, simply enter the following to run holbash:
.P
.RS
.B ./hsh
.P
.RE
This will begin your simple_shell session. To end your session, enter the command 'exit' or press 'Ctrl+D' or 'Ctrl+Z'. 'Ctrl+C' functionality IS DISABLED.
Non-interactive mode is also supported, along with piping and scripting. Please refer to 'man sh' for more information on this type of functionality!
.SH BUILTINS
.P
.RS
.B  env
- Writes environmental variables to output
.P
.B  exit
- Replaces Ctrl+C, terminates holbash
.PP
.P
.B #
- User can add comments after typing '#'

.SH BUGS
None, less functionality than a normal shell
